abstract: Officials in both states raced to contact people who might have been exposed to the coronavirus, and experts warned that the cases could indicate signs of spread within the United States.
snippet: Officials in both states raced to contact people who might have been exposed to the coronavirus, and experts warned that the cases could indicate signs of spread within the United States.
lead_paragraph: [This briefing has ended. Read the latest updates on the coronavirus here.]

abstract: Schools across the United States are canceling trips abroad, preparing online lessons and even rethinking “perfect attendance” awards as they brace for the possibility that the  new coronavirus could begin spreading in their communities.

headline_main: US Schools Start Planning for Possible Spread of Coronavirus

abstract: The coronavirus spread further on Friday, with cases reported for the first time in at least six countries across four continents, battering markets and leading the World Health Organization (WHO) to raise its impact risk alert to "very high."
snippet: The coronavirus spread further on Friday, with cases reported for the first time in at least six countries across four continents, battering markets and leading the World Health Organization (WHO) to raise its impact risk alert to "very high."
lead_paragraph: GENEVA/BEIJING — The coronavirus spread further on Friday, with cases reported for the first time in at least six countries across four continents, battering markets and leading the World Health Organization (WHO) to raise its impact risk alert to "very high."
headline_main: Global Downturn Looms as Countries Struggle to Contain Coronavirus Outbreak
headline_print_headline: Global Downturn Looms as Countries Struggle to Contain Coronavirus Outbreak

abstract: Refugees in Turkey headed toward European frontiers on Friday after an official said the borders had been thrown open, a  response to the escalating war in Syria where 33 Turkish soldiers were killed by Russian-backed Syrian government troops.
snippet: Refugees in Turkey headed toward European frontiers on Friday after an official said the borders had been thrown open, a  response to the escalating war in Syria where 33 Turkish soldiers were killed by Russian-backed Syrian government troops.
lead_paragraph: OUTSIDE SARAQEB, Syria/ANKARA — Refugees in Turkey headed toward European frontiers on Friday after an official said the borders had been thrown open, a response to the escalating war in Syria where 33 Turkish soldiers were killed by Russian-backed Syrian government troops.
headline_main: Turkey Says It Will Let Refugees Into Europe After Its Troops Killed in Syria
headline_print_headline: Turkey Says It Will Let Refugees Into Europe After Its Troops Killed in Syria

abstract: President Donald Trump has decided not to take action on imports of titanium sponge, a key input in military aircraft, after a Commerce Department investigation found imports hurt U.S. makers of the material and threaten national security, a memo showed.
snippet: President Donald Trump has decided not to take action on imports of titanium sponge, a key input in military aircraft, after a Commerce Department investigation found imports hurt U.S. makers of the material and threaten national security, a memo ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump has decided not to take action on imports of titanium sponge, a key input in military aircraft, after a Commerce Department investigation found imports hurt U.S. makers of the material and threaten national security, a memo showed.
headline_main: Trump Eyes Talks With Japan to Ensure Access to Titanium Sponge
headline_print_headline: Trump Eyes Talks With Japan to Ensure Access to Titanium Sponge

abstract: President Donald Trump on Thursday cited low unemployment rates for African Americans and passage of a criminal justice bill providing earlier release for thousands of federal drug offenders as examples of how he’s helping the black community.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Thursday cited low unemployment rates for African Americans and passage of a criminal justice bill providing earlier release for thousands of federal drug offenders as examples of how he’s helping the black community.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Thursday cited low unemployment rates for African Americans and passage of a criminal justice bill providing earlier release for thousands of federal drug offenders as examples of how he’s helping the black community.
headline_main: Trump Meets With Black Supporters, Vows Equal Opportunity
headline_print_headline: Trump Meets With Black Supporters, Vows Equal Opportunity

abstract: United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres called women's inequality "stupid" and a cause for global shame on Thursday, as he pledged to press governments to end discriminatory laws in the face of a "strong and relentless pushback" against women's rights.
snippet: United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres called women's inequality "stupid" and a cause for global shame on Thursday, as he pledged to press governments to end discriminatory laws in the face of a "strong and relentless pushback" against ...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - United Nations Secretary-General Antonio Guterres called women's inequality "stupid" and a cause for global shame on Thursday, as he pledged to press governments to end discriminatory laws in the face of a "strong and relentless pushback" against women's rights.
headline_main: U.N. Chief Declares Women's Inequality 'Stupid' and a Global Shame
headline_print_headline: U.N. Chief Declares Women's Inequality 'Stupid' and a Global Shame

abstract: President Donald Trump's choice of Vice President Mike Pence to oversee the nation's response to the new coronavirus threat is bringing renewed scrutiny to the former governor's handling of an HIV outbreak in southern Indiana when he was governor.
snippet: President Donald Trump's choice of Vice President Mike Pence to oversee the nation's response to the new coronavirus threat is bringing renewed scrutiny to the former governor's handling of an HIV outbreak in southern Indiana when he was governor.
lead_paragraph: INDIANAPOLIS — President Donald Trump's choice of Vice President Mike Pence to oversee the nation's response to the new coronavirus threat is bringing renewed scrutiny to the former governor's handling of an HIV outbreak in southern Indiana when he was governor.
headline_main: Pence's Handling of 2015 HIV Outbreak Gets New Scrutiny
headline_print_headline: Pence's Handling of 2015 HIV Outbreak Gets New Scrutiny

abstract: After an airstrike on Turkish forces by Russia or its Syrian allies, President Trump may be forced to pick between Moscow and Ankara.
snippet: After an airstrike on Turkish forces by Russia or its Syrian allies, President Trump may be forced to pick between Moscow and Ankara.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has long sought to avoid confronting the leaders of Turkey and Russia — two foreign strongmen who are facing off in civil wars in Syria and Libya. But after an airstrike on Thursday that killed dozens of Turkish troops in northwest Syria, Mr. Trump may be forced to pick a side.
